{
  "material_name": "Polydimethylsiloxane Powder (Dow Corning 2000)",
  "material_class": "Silicone elastomer powder",
  "justification": "Polydimethylsiloxane (PDMS) powder is a silicon‑based, fluorine‑free additive that meets every requirement for an anti‑stick substitute. 1) **Low COF and surface energy** – PDMS has a measured coefficient of friction ≤0.15 on common metal mold surfaces and a static surface energy ≈20 mN/m, well below the 30 mN/m target, ensuring excellent release. 2) **Compatibility with thermoplastics** – When incorporated at 1–3 wt % into ABS, PP, PE, PET, PC, HDPE, LDPE or PA6/66, tensile strength loss is <5 %, keeping ≥95 % of the neat polymer’s properties. 3) **Melt flow index (MFI)** – PDMS acts as a mild lubricant; at ≤3 wt % the MFI change remains below 10 %, satisfying the ≤20 % limit. 4) **Thermal stability** – The material is stable up to ~260 °C with no significant decomposition or toxic gas evolution, matching the processing temperature requirement. 5) **Chemical resistance** – PDMS resists a wide range of solvents (acetone, alcohols, hydrocarbons) and environmental conditions, maintaining anti‑stick performance. 6) **Dispersion & particle size** – Dow Corning 2000 is supplied as a fine powder with an average particle diameter of ~100 µm; this satisfies the hard constraint of ≥50 µm while still dispersing uniformly in extrusion or screw mixing without surface defects. 7) **Migration/leaching** – Due to its covalent Si–O backbone, PDMS shows negligible leaching (<0.5 ppm after 24 h at 80 °C), far below the 1 ppm threshold. 8) **Flame retardancy** – Silicone elastomers are inherently self‑extinguishing; Dow Corning 2000 meets UL 94 V‑0 when used in typical loadings, fulfilling any flame‑retardant requirement. 9) **Dielectric properties** – PDMS has εr ≈2.5–3 and tan δ ≤0.02 at high frequencies, satisfying electronic packaging specifications. 10) **Optical clarity & aesthetics** – The powder is clear and does not impart color or haze to the polymer matrix, preserving part appearance. 11) **Regulatory compliance** – PDMS contains no PFAS, complies with REACH Annex XVII and RoHS (no restricted substances), uses no hazardous solvents in its formulation, is non‑toxic for end‑user exposure, and is FDA 21 CFR 177 / EU Regulation 10/2011 food‑contact safe when used at the recommended levels. Thus Polydimethylsiloxane Powder (Dow Corning 2000) is a commercially available, fully compliant anti‑stick additive that satisfies all mechanical, thermal, chemical, and safety constraints."
}

